               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-840" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-840" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-840" type="surname" value="PLUMMER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-840" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY PLUMMER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Golden-lane—my brother John is the owner of the manufactory; the prisoner was in his service. On the night of the 24th of Sept. I fastened the door of the manufactory and the store-room—I left at a quarter past eight o'clock—I came on Monday morning, and found the cupboard broken open by a chisel or some instrument, and the chisel in the cupboard.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-841" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-841" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-841" type="surname" value="DYER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-841" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN DYER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to John Plummer. About half-past eight o'clock this evening my mistress gave me 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. in copper, in a brown paper—I put it into the cupboard in the store-room—I am sure it was put in safe, and the door fast—on the Monday morning I went to the store-room at a quarter past eight, and the cupboard was broken open, and the money gone—the prisoner ought to have arrived about six on the Monday morning.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-842" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-842" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-842" type="surname" value="BURKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-842" type="given" value="ALICE"></interp>ALICE BURKE</persName>
                  </hi>. I had the key of the store-room on Saturday night—I got there about six o'clock on Monday morning—the prisoner came for the key about seven—I gave him the key, which enabled him to get into the store-room.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-843" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-843" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-843" type="surname" value="ADAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-843" type="given" value="JOHN ROBERT"></interp>JOHN ROBERT ADAMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am employed in the manufactory. I received information between eight and nine o'clock, and went in pursuit of the pri<lb></lb>soner—he ought to have been at work on Monday morning—he was gone—I went after him—I overtook him, and asked why he did not come to work—he said he was ill—I said, "You are accused of taking a 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. paper of half<lb></lb>pence out of the cupboard"—he denied it—I felt about, and took 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. and some odd pence, in penny-pieces, from his trowsers pocket.</p>
